			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="952">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>Joe Wilkins&rsquo;s tribute to ten of his father figures [&ldquo;<a href="/article/4331">You, All of You</a>,&rdquo; September 2009] hit me right in the heart and reminded me again why I look forward to your magazine each month. I&rsquo;m past my sixtieth birthday and have raised two sons, and I can tell Wilkins that the search for a father doesn&rsquo;t end. We patch them in, these surrogate fathers. Sometimes it&rsquo;s a good thing, and other times it makes more trouble for everyone. I haven&rsquo;t found any wisdom in the search, only noticed how it plays out in my life.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Cathy Smith<br>Ashland, Oregon</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

					</div>

